overhear /ˌəʊvəˈhɪə/

(overhearing,overheard,overhears) 

1. V-T If you overhear someone, you hear what they are saying when they are not talking to you and they do not know that you are listening. 无意中听到 

例： I overheard two doctors discussing my case. 我无意中听到两个医生在讨论我的病例。

